<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-012-201 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 522 923</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 12 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Smith Micro launches HotFax software. (Smith Micro Software Inc.)andO;(Product Announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Smith Micro Software Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   HotFax (Communications software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFacsimileCommunications software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Smith Micro Launches HotFax Software 11/12/91 HUNTINGTON BEACH, CALIFORNIA,U.S.A., 1991 NOV 12 (NB) -- Smith Micro Software, which acquired the Hotlineline of memory resident phone books last year, has launched HotFax, completewith both fax and data communications support.andM;HotFax supports all the common fax board &quot;standards,&quot; including SendFax,Class 1, Class 2, and the DCA/Intel CAS specification.andP;  The data side of theproduct supports all Hayes-compatible modems.andM;The company claims that, when used with HotLine, HotFax provides a completeanswer for telephone, fax, and modem management.andP;  It is based on Smith's ownQuickLink II Fax S/R product, which is shipped with many fax modems.andM;The new product is an upgrade for QuickLink with more features and power.andP;  Itincludes FastFax V, a utility which can be brought up from any MS-DOSapplication and allows for the sending of a fax as though it were a printfunction.andP;  A set of 25 soft fonts is included with the program.andM;Separate phone lists can also be maintained for data and fax telephonenumbers, using the popular dBase file structure.andP;  The FaxUSA ElectronicDirectory of 110,000 fax numbers, also by Smith Micro, can also be used withthe product.andP;  It retails for $149.95 and ships in December.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19911112/Press Contact: Bill Smith, Smith Micro Software,714-964-0412)</TEXT></DOC>